COMMENT: Unique identifier assigned by Cybersyn to each company.
The state or province of the registrant.
Central Index Key (CIK). Ten digit number assigned by the SEC to each registrant that submits filings.
Standard Industrial Classification (SIC). Code assigned by the SEC indicating the registrant industry group.
Name of registrant. This corresponds to the name of the legal entity as of the latest filing date.
A unique identifier of the state where the business is headquartered. Joinable to the GEOGRAPHY_INDEX table
Employee Identification Number assigned by the Internal Revenue Service (IRS)
A unique identifier of the country where the business is headquartered. Joinable to the GEOGRAPHY_INDEX table
